 <span class=\"str_py\">[ <a href=\"allsetlearning-sha1.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone1\">shā</a> ]</span> <span class=\"str_desc\">sand, gravel, pebbles; granulated</span></li>\n          <li><span class=\"str_def\"><a class=\"dictips\">衣</a></span> <span class=\"str_py\">[ <a href=\"allsetlearning-yi1.mp3\" class=\"pinyin tone1\">yī</a> ]</span> <span class=\"str_desc\">cloth; clothes, apparel; dress, coat</span></li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<hr><span id=\"purpleculture_examples\">①(袈裟)见“袈”。</span>\n<hr>\n<div>\n  <div><b>Chinese Definition:</b>\n    <div><b>Pictophonetic</b>: <span class=\"semantic\"><a class=\"dictips\">沙</a></span> indicates the sound; <span class=\"phonetic\"><a class=\"dictips\">衣</a></span> (cloth) conveys the meaning.</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div>Freq: 4784</div>\n<hr><span><span style=\"color:#1ce63d\">Kanshudo mnemonic:</span>the clothes (<a href=\"/kanji/%E8%A1%A3\">衣</a>) of sand (<a href=\"/kanji/%E6%B2%99\">沙</a>) are a Buddhist robe</span>\n<hr>\n<div></div>\n<div>\n  <hr>\n</div>\n<div class=\"two_children__horiz_even\">\n  <div id=\"baidu_chinese\">\n    <div>裟，读作：shā。汉字常用组词“<a href=\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E8%A2%88%E8%A3%9F/570200\">袈裟</a>”（ jiā shā）：<a href=\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E5%92%8C%E5%B0%9A/189974\">和尚</a>披在外面的一种法衣。</div>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"baidu_chinese_en\">\n    <div>裟, pronounced: shā. The commonly used group of Chinese characters is &quot;<a href=\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E8%A2%88%E8%A3%9F/570200\">袈裟</a>&quot; (jiā shā): a vestige worn by <a href=\"https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E5%92%8C%E5%B0%9A/189974\">monks</a> .</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"hanziyuan\">\n  <div class=\"etymology-nav\" id=\"&#x88DF;\">\n    <div class=\"alert alert-success etymology-alert m-0\" role=\"alert\"></div>\n    <div class=\"row bg-info border-purple border-top mx-0 row-eq-height\" id=\"E05403\">\n      <div class=\"col-md-3 col-sm-4 p-0\">\n        <div class=\"p-1\">\n       